 of these agreements recognizes the unique qualities possessed by VMI graduates and provides certain benefits to VMI alumni applying to these programs  including guaranteed interviews and application fee waivers  Norwich University in Vermont also has an MOU agreement with VMI that provides alumni a 10  tuition reduction and a few waiver for its online graduate programs  including programs in business and public administration  Norwich is especially interested in serving active duty members of the military  For information on any of these agreements  please contact Ltc  Barry Cobb at cobbbr vmi edu   Spring 2012 Newsletter  Field Test  Faculty Research  New Faculty  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  BGS Activity  Fed Challenge  Cadet Awards  Col  Bush   2015 Advisor  Memo of Understanding  Alumni Survey  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 